2.caption: 1963 East–West Pro Bowl
2.description: The 1963 Pro Bowl was the National Football League's thirteenth annual all-star game which featured the outstanding performers from the 1962 season. The game was played on January 13, 1963, at the Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum in Los Angeles, California in front of 61,374 fans. The Eastern Conference was coached by Allie Sherman of the New York Giants and the West by Vince Lombardi of the Green Bay Packers.
2.inspected:Co-MVPs: Jim Brown (Cleveland Browns), Eugene Lipscomb (Pittsburgh Steelers)
